### Create a product
POST http://localhost:8080/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "SKU-001",
  "name": "Cordless Drill",
  "description": "18V cordless drill with two batteries"
}

### Get all products
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products

### Get one product
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/1

### Update a product
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/products/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sku": "SKU-001",
  "name": "Cordless Drill (updated)",
  "description": "Now with a carrying case"
}

### Delete a product
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/products/1

### Create a warehouse
POST http://localhost:8080/api/warehouses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "WH-PAD-01",
  "name": "Paderborn Central Warehouse",
  "city": "Paderborn"
}

### Get all warehouses
GET http://localhost:8080/api/warehouses

### Get one warehouse
GET http://localhost:8080/api/warehouses/1

### (If needed) create a product first
POST http://localhost:8080/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{ "sku": "SKU-100", "name": "Safety Helmet", "description": "Hard hat, yellow" }

### Register stock — product in warehouse 1
POST http://localhost:8080/api/stock
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "quantity": 50 }

### Register the same product in warehouse 2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/stock
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 3, "warehouseId": 2, "quantity": 20 }

### View all stock
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock

### View stock in warehouse 1 only
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock?warehouseId=1

### Try a duplicate — should return 409
POST http://localhost:8080/api/stock
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "quantity": 5 }

### Receive 30 units into warehouse 1 (INBOUND)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "type": "INBOUND", "quantity": 30 }

### Check the stock level went UP
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock?warehouseId=1

### Pick 10 units out (OUTBOUND)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "type": "OUTBOUND", "quantity": 10 }

### Check the stock level went DOWN
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock?warehouseId=1

### Try to over-pick — should return 409 with a clear message
POST http://localhost:8080/api/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "type": "OUTBOUND", "quantity": 99999 }

### Full movement history (newest first)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/movements

### History for one product
GET http://localhost:8080/api/movements?productId=2

### Low-stock with default threshold (10)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock/low-stock

### Low-stock with a custom threshold
GET http://localhost:8080/api/stock/low-stock?threshold=25

### Bad movement — quantity must be positive
POST http://localhost:8080/api/movements
Content-Type: application/json

{ "productId": 2, "warehouseId": 1, "type": "OUTBOUND", "quantity": -5 }

### Bad product — should return a clean 400
POST http://localhost:8080/api/products
Content-Type: application/json

{ "sku": "", "name": "" }